The Elauus melanopterus appears to be spread over a vast extent of the Old World, being numerous in Egypt, and the greater part of Africa, as far as to the Cape ofGood Hope. It has also been met with in various parts of India, in Jam, and New Holland. There seems to be a considerable variation in the plumage of this species, the black markings of the wing spread- ing to a greater or less extent in different specimens.
